      "content": "{\"claim\": \"Harness strictly beats self-consistency when the candidate error rate e is within a steep-transition window 1/(k+2) > e > 1/(k+3) for odd k≥7 AND the critic achieves precision P > e+0.1 and recall R > 0.9 on the subset of pools where the majority share is exactly M = floor(k/2)+1. Under these conditions, the critic removes more minimal-margin incorrect majorities than minimal-margin correct majorities, yielding net positive benefit.\", \"mechanism\": \"Let M = floor(k/2)+1 be the SC majority threshold. At error rate e near 1/(k+2), the probability of a minimal-margin majority (share = M) is maximized. The critic acts as a binary classifier on these exact-threshold pools. The expected net benefit = R·P_inc·N_inc - FPR·P_cor·N_cor, where P_inc = fraction of minimal pools that are incorrect, P_cor = fraction that are correct. Near e = 1/(k+2) for k=7, P_inc ≈ 0.31, P_cor ≈ 0.69. For net benefit > 0: R·0.31 > (1-P)·0.69. Simplifying: if R > 0.9 and P > e+0.1, the critic’s high recall captures incorrect minimal majorities while precision margins prevent false breaks, guaranteeing net benefit on the minimal subset.\", \"scope\": {\"covers\": [\"odd k ≥ 7\", \"e ∈ (1/(k+3), 1/(k+2))\", \"P > e+0.1 AND R > 0.9 on minimal-majority subset\", \"binary-answer questions only\"], \"excludes\": [\"k ≤ 5\", \"e ≥ 1/(k+2) (wider margin regime)\", \"e ≤ 1/(k+3) (near-deterministic regime)\", \"P ≤ e+0.1 (critic no better than chance)\", \"multi-answer questions where plurality ≠ majority\"]}, \"forbidden\": [{\"case\": \"At k=7, e≈0.10, P>0.20, R>0.90: harness - SC ≤ 0 across all tested sub-bands\", \"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}, {\"case\": \"Net fixed-minus-broken ≤ 0 when P > e+0.1 and R > 0.9 on the minimal-majority subset\", \"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}, {\"case\": \"Harness improvement is uncorrelated with the fraction of minimal-majority pools in the sample (Spearman ρ < 0.3, p > 0.05)\", \"eval\": \"rubric:std-crit-design\"}], \"prose_notes\": \"This candidate narrows the margin definition to exact threshold hits. P > e+0.1 and R > 0.9 are necessary AND sufficient because the critic needs high recall to catch rare minimal incorrect majorities. The experiment should use a difficulty-targeted question set (not random sampling) to ensure enough questions fall in the e ≈ 1/(k+2) band. With 200 questions at k=7 (1400 candidate calls + 200 critic calls + 200 SC calls ≈ 1800 calls), this fits within 300k tokens if questions are concise.\"}",
